article_title: Cleanup Continues After Tornado Sweeps Through Tulsa Area - News9.com - Oklahoma City, OK - News, Weather, Video and Sports
article_text:
Cleanup continues in north Tulsa after a tornado touched down Wednesday evening.

EMSA reports there have been no additional weather-related injuries, so the numbered injured in Wednesday's storms remains at seven.

Also, all Tulsa Public Schools will be in session today after four were canceled on Thursday.

3/31/2016 Related Story: Tornado Damage Extensive In North Tulsa Neighborhoods
